target.comment:
At least 10% reduction in silt in the Pangani River system;


At least 25% reduction in erosion gulleys and rills


At least 25% increase in ground cover (grasslands and woody vegetation) for highly degraded patches under rehabilitation;

actual.comment:
This indicator has been exceeded for crops like banana and coffee whose average increase for the region is 81% (42 to 65 tonnes/ha) and 60% (2 to 3 t/ha) respectively among the households that participate in the project. For other crops, however, e.g., maize, beans, and paddy, the increases have not reached the target, 39% (10 to 19 t/ha), 7% (2.5 to 3.9 t/ha), and 7% (4.2 to 4.7 t/ha) respectively.  Details for each district are given below:

 In Moshi DC, crop productivity has increased due to increase of soil fertility and soil moisture conservation after sub soiling and layout and construction of contour terraces in 61 villages. Maize production before SLM was 2 tonnes/ha but after SLM production increased to 4 tonnes/ha (sub soiling technology), coffee production was 0.13 tonne/ ha before SLM Project intervention and after SLM production increased a little to 0.80 tonne/ha and banana production was 10 tonnes/ha  before SLM and increased to 14 tonnes/ha after SLM intervention. Coffee increased from 0.1 to 0.8 t/ha;

 In Moshi Municipal Council-before project intervention production of maize was 2.7 t/ha, but after intervention production change to 3.0 (11%). Paddy rice production was 4.2 tonnes /ha, after intervention production increase to 4.5 tonnes/ha (7%);

 Hai district, yield 2.6 tonnes of maize/ha, 1.8 tonnes/ha of beans, 17.7 tonnes/ha of bananas, and 0.9 tonnes of coffee/ha;

 In Siha, amongst households participating in the project, banana yield increased from 3.0 to 12.0 tonnes/ha, maize 1.6 to 4.5 tonnes/ha and coffee 0.2 to 0.3 tonnes/ha;

 In Rombo, banana yield was 11.3 t/ha prior to the project, it is now 12.0 t/ha. Maize yield improved from 0.6 to 1.0 t/ha, but coffee and beans remained constant at 0.2 and 0.1 t/ha respectively;

  In Mwanga, crop yields changes (1.4 to 9.0 t/ha of banana, 0.4 to 2.0 t/ha of maize, 0.8 to 1.0 t/ha of coffee, and 0.1 to 0.8 t/ha of beans); and

 Changes in crop yield in Same (1.0 to 1.2 t/ha of bananas, 0.7 to 1.4 t/ha of maize, and 0.6 to 1.2 t/ha of beans.


For non-benefitting families yields are as follows:

 2.5 tonnes/ha of maize, 0.13 tonnes/ha coffee, and 12 tonnes/ha bananas in Moshi DC. 

 maize is 2.7 tonnes/ha, and 4.2 tonnes/ha of rice in Moshi Municipality

 for maize in Hai, yield is 2.2 tonnes/ha, for beans 1.6 tonnes/ha, bananas 15.3 tonnes /ha, coffee 0.77 tonnes/ha while participating households

 in Siha, banana, maize and coffee were 3.0, 1.0 and 0.2 tonnes/ha respectively

 In Rombo, banana is 11.3 t/ha, maize is 0.6, coffee and beans are 0.2 and 0.1 t/ha respectively;

 In Mwanga, the yields are static (1.4, 0.4, 0.8, and 0.1 t/ha of banana, maize, coffee, ad beans respectively); and

 In same the yields are still 1.0, 0.7, and 0.6 t/ha of bananas, maize, and beans respectively
